</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7D006424BD874DF5FA14C9AFB392AC1A" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<taxonomicName id="81D140924AFE627D1E1E8625DE217716" authorityName="Jost, Oleas &amp; Meerow" authorityYear="2015" class="Tentaculata" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Eucharis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eucharis ruthiana" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Ctenophora" rank="species" species="ruthiana">
<emphasis id="DBFBD8D50CD1FF6FC868B9DB90374D06" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Eucharis ruthiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appears closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="A8B00CB1B0BAA18B731260E22CFB5E78" authorityName="Meerow" authorityYear="1987" baseAuthorityName="Baker" class="Tentaculata" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Eucharis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eucharis moorei" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Ctenophora" rank="species" species="moorei">
<emphasis id="136C55FDD06C0301413B4A7A7B4B3596" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Eucharis moorei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Baker) Meerow (
<bibRefCitation id="F5578E30F9B9F32F2B58DEB2EB42F4A0" author="Meerow, AW" journalOrPublisher="Sida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="29 - 49" refId="B3" refString="Meerow, AW, 1987a. New species of Phaedranassa and Eucharis (Amaryllidaceae). Sida 12: 29 - 49" title="New species of Phaedranassa and Eucharis (Amaryllidaceae)." volume="12" year="1987 a">Meerow 1987a</bibRefCitation>
), placing it in 
<taxonomicName id="4B51A8180EE64E330112B2B0D3E90D3B" class="Tentaculata" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Eucharis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eucharis (Heterocharis) subsp. subg." order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Ctenophora" rank="subGenus" species="moorei" subGenus="Heterocharis" subSpecies="subg.">Eucharis subg. Heterocharis</taxonomicName>
Meerow, characterized by large campanulate, fragrant flowers, numerous ovules per locule, and green mature capsules (
<bibRefCitation id="7841363C96C81D8F5646FF54300AB1F9" author="Meerow, AW" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="136 - 220" publicationUrl="10.2307/2399347" refId="B5" refString="Meerow, AW, 1989. Systematics of the Amazon lilies, Eucharis and Caliphruria (Amaryllidaceae). Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden 76: 136 - 220, DOI: 10.2307/2399347" title="Systematics of the Amazon lilies, Eucharis and Caliphruria (Amaryllidaceae)." url="10.2307/2399347" volume="76" year="1989">Meerow 1989</bibRefCitation>
). It differs from this species by the narrower leaves and tepals, mild (vs. strong) fragrance, deeply cleft staminal corona with long marginal teeth, the incurved free filaments, and the short style (Table 
<tableCitation id="A96840EB51F62EF762F3FD87C84C2350" captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="T2" captionText="Table 2. Contrasting features of Eucharis ruthiana and Eucharis moorei." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/E4C8D089BB739D0F973740919AFAC572" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" tableUuid="E4C8D089BB739D0F973740919AFAC572">2</tableCitation>
). From the putative hybrid 
<taxonomicName id="62F8E1138588157904CC9DD214132C54" class="Tentaculata" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Eucharis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eucharis grandiflora" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Ctenophora" rank="species" species="grandiflora">
Eucharis 
<normalizedToken id="177C80E99886E08030B383924FA97041" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
grandiflora
</taxonomicName>
Planch. &amp; Lind., (1853) it differs by the long staminal teeth and its fertility.
</paragraph>
<caption id="E4C8D089BB739D0F973740919AFAC572" ID-Table-UUID="E4C8D089BB739D0F973740919AFAC572" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/E4C8D089BB739D0F973740919AFAC572" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" start="Table 2" startId="T2">
<paragraph id="D16659A2EAA8A2C865E70EF007D3D82D" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis id="2A1AC62EFCC37BD3A0292544138168E6" bold="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Table 2.</emphasis>
Contrasting features of 
<taxonomicName id="7F0A8A00930FB5960F0ED519941CCF00" authorityName="Jost, Oleas &amp; Meerow" authorityYear="2015" class="Tentaculata" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Eucharis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eucharis ruthiana" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Ctenophora" rank="species" species="ruthiana">
<emphasis id="8AF779E2E922608725E5BD315199B85D" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Eucharis ruthiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F0F048599430CE602D4EE14852B682C4" authorityName="Meerow" authorityYear="1987" baseAuthorityName="Baker" class="Tentaculata" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Eucharis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Eucharis moorei" order="Asparagales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Ctenophora" rank="species" species="moorei">
<emphasis id="CA48DF94E5E2D57BF4464B77E80E9068" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Eucharis moorei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
